title: Phlebotomist
description:
**Overview**  
Join our dynamic healthcare team as a Phlebotomist, where your skills in specimen collection will make a significant impact on the lives of those we serve. You will play a vital role in ensuring accurate blood sampling and processing, in a clinical setting. Your expertise in laboratory procedures and techniques will be essential.

**What you’ll do**

* Perform venipuncture and blood sampling with precision and care, ensuring patient comfort throughout the process.
* Collect, label, and process specimens according to established protocols, maintaining the highest standards of aseptic technique.
* Provide excellent patient service by communicating effectively with patients about procedures and addressing any concerns they may have.
* Collaborate with laboratory staff to ensure accurate specimen handling and timely processing of samples.
* Maintain cleanliness and organization of the laboratory environment, adhering to safety regulations at all times.
* Stay current with medical terminology, anatomy, and physiology knowledge to enhance patient interactions and improve service delivery.

**Basic qualifications**

\\* Certification required

* Proven experience in laboratory procedures and techniques related to phlebotomy.

**Preferred qualifications**

* Clinical laboratory experience in a hospital or healthcare setting.
* Strong understanding of medical terminology related to blood collection and specimen processing.
* Familiarity with anatomy knowledge that supports effective venipuncture practices.

**Why you’ll love it here**  
We are dedicated to fostering an environment where our employees can thrive both personally and professionally.

**About us**  
As part of our healthcare team, you will contribute to our mission of delivering exceptional patient care through skilled practices in phlebotomy. We believe in empowering our employees by creating an inclusive environment that recognizes their contributions while enhancing the health of our community every day. Join us in making a difference!

title: Certified Nursing Assistant-Weekends
description:
Apply today and meet our recruiter, Kiara Dickens, who's been a Registered Nurse for 10 years and understands the importance of having financial stability, a flexible schedule, and a workplace that cares.

Starting at $17/hr \\- $18/hr. with an excellent work environment (including 24/7 support) and full\\-time or part\\-time available for caregiving positions in South Hillsborough County and the surrounding areas!

Benefits

* Competitive wages: $17/hr to $18/hr
* Comprehensive support, 24/7
* Training, ongoing education, and orientation

Our Mission

When our founder's parents developed dementia, she decided to drop everything and take care of them full\\-time. She doesn't want other families to feel under the same burden. We understand that caring for those most in need in our community lifts a huge burden.

Our Ideal Candidate

We're seeking compassionate individuals for caregiving roles. We offer a robust training program for both experienced and new caregivers. Enjoy a supportive work environment with full\\-time and part\\-time positions available in South Hillsborough County.

Job Responsibilities

* Assist clients with **activities of daily living (ADLs)**, including bathing, dressing, grooming, toileting, feeding, and mobility.
* Provide **personal hygiene care** such as oral care, skin care, hair care, and nail care (non\\-clinical).
* Assist with **ambulation, transfers, and range\\-of\\-motion exercises** as instructed by the care plan.
* Perform **light housekeeping** duties such as laundry, meal preparation, and maintaining a clean, safe environment.
* Take and record **vital signs** (temperature, pulse, respiration, and blood pressure) as directed.
* Observe and report **changes in client condition** or unusual incidents promptly to the supervising nurse or care coordinator.
* Provide **companionship** and emotional support to clients and families.
* Follow the client’s **care plan** and agency policies and procedures.
* Maintain **accurate documentation** of care provided, observations, and client activities.
* Adhere to **infection control and safety protocols** at all times.
* Participate in **ongoing training and competency evaluations**.

Requirements

* **Current CNA certification** (state\\-approved and active).
* **High school diploma or GED** required.
* **CPR and First Aid certification** (current).
* **Valid driver’s license and reliable transportation** (if travel is required).
* Previous **home care or long\\-term care experience** preferred.
* Excellent communication, observation, and time\\-management skills.
* Compassionate, dependable, and able to work independently.
* Treat clients with dignity and respect
* Weekend availability (If applicable)
* Effective communication skills
* Valid driver's license and auto insurance (If applicable)
* Level 2 Background Check
* Compliance with State of Florida regulations, DMV check, and drug screening.

title: Staff Physical Therapy Assistant
description:
**PTA with Purpose**

At Renew Integrative Physical Therapy, we believe that true healing for patients begins with humility, service, and purpose. We are a Christ\\-centered, self\\-pay orthopedic practice committed to honoring God in our work, putting others before ourselves, and restoring people to full wellness. This is more than a job — it’s a calling.

The medical system is broken and as reimbursements go down and the need for wholistic healing increases, there is a great need for a different kind of healing through physical therapy. Physical therapy assistants are already being replaced by A.I., online exercise protocols and other professions such as massage therapy. Only the PTs who invest in themselves and train to approach healing differently will be able to meet the demands of a changing healthcare climate.

We believe we are that industry disrupter that our system needs – not by chasing titles or status, but by becoming excellent in both skill and spirit. We are looking for remarkable individuals with strong character, a heart for service, and a relentless pursuit of growth — not simply years of experience.

If you are ready to grow into the clinician and person you were meant to be, read on.

**Physical Therapist Assistant Opportunity Highlights**

* **Clinical Mentorship \\& Mastery**: Train in advanced, cutting\\-edge techniques that go beyond traditional PTA school curriculum. With deep mentorship and a focus on integrative healing, our team is elevated into the top 1% of clinicians in the country — both in outcomes and income.
* **Earn While You Learn:** We believe “high requirements deserve high reward.” That’s why we provide full compensation and benefits even during training, so you can grow without the burden of financial stress.
* **Leadership Development \\& Ownership Pathways:** We don’t just teach you how to treat — we equip you to lead. You’ll gain business acumen, leadership tools, and even the opportunity to open your own practice within our network, if that’s your calling.

**Who is Renew?**

Renew Integrative Physical Therapy is a true industry disruptor – not because we chase trends, but because we return to what matters most: outcomes for clients. We put patients before paperwork and purpose above profit. Every decision we make is grounded in honoring God, serving others with compassion, and delivering exceptional outcomes.

We seek to understand the root cause of dysfunction and provide care that brings lasting healing, not just temporary relief. Our model empowers clinicians to spend quality time with patients, apply advanced techniques like Fascial Counterstrain, and solve the complex problems others overlook.

At Renew, excellence isn’t a buzzword — it’s a culture. We attract physical therapist assistants who are hungry for growth, willing to be sharpened, and ready to lead a new standard of care. This is where mission meets mastery. If you're ready to make a difference and rise to your full potential, you're in the right place.

**Do You Have What It Takes to Join Renew?**

* **Full Commitment** – There is no halfway. We serve wholeheartedly.
* **Confidence** – Know what you know. Own what you don’t.
* **Humility** – Be teachable, flexible, and eager to grow.
* **Grit** – This path is not easy, but it’s worth it.

**Next Steps**

Only apply if you resonate with this mission and meet the criteria above. To be considered, please submit your resume and a cover letter that answers the following:

* Where do you see yourself in 5–10 years?
* What values are most important to you in an employer?
* What do you know about Fascial Counterstrain (if anything)?

**A Final Note**

We receive many applications and accept very few. If we don’t contact you, please know we are grateful for your interest and may reach out when a future opening aligns. We do not hire resumes — we hire people. People who are bold in faith, humble in heart, relentless in pursuit, and deeply aligned with our mission to bring true healing to the world.

title: Certified Coder
description:
**Job Overview**  
We are seeking a detail\\-oriented and highly skilled Family Medicine Certified Coder to join our healthcare team. The ideal candidate will possess a thorough understanding of medical coding practices, CPT (Current Procedural Terminology) coding, and ICD (International Classification of Diseases) coding systems such as ICD\\-10\\. As a Certified Coder, you will be responsible for reviewing the accuracy of medical records into standardized codes to facilitate precise billing, reimbursement, and data analysis. Your expertise will ensure compliance with healthcare regulations and contribute to the efficient operation of our medical billing processes. This position offers an engaging opportunity for professionals committed to accuracy, compliance, and improving healthcare documentation.

Please note this is an onsite position. Requests for REMOTE work will not be taken into consideration.

**Responsibilities**

* Review and analyze medical records to assign appropriate diagnostic and procedural codes using ICD\\-10 and CPT systems.
* Ensure all coding is accurate, complete, and compliant with current regulatory guidelines and payer requirements.
* Collaborate with medical billers and collectors to facilitate seamless billing processes and resolve discrepancies promptly.
* Maintain detailed documentation of coding activities within Electronic Medical Record (EMR) or Electronic Health Record (EHR) systems.
* Stay updated on changes in coding standards, healthcare regulations, and insurance policies affecting medical coding practices.
* Assist in auditing medical records for accuracy and completeness to support proper reimbursement and legal documentation.
* Support the training of new staff members on coding protocols and documentation standards as needed.
* Contribute to the improvement of clinical documentation by providing feedback on record completeness and accuracy.
* Participate in ongoing education to enhance knowledge of medical terminology, coding updates, and billing procedures.

**Experience**

* Proven experience in medical coding within a healthcare setting, specifically Family Medicine.
* Strong understanding of medical terminology, anatomy, physiology, and healthcare documentation standards.
* Experience working with EMR or EHR systems for accurate data entry and record management.
* Knowledge of medical billing processes and procedures related to insurance claims submission and collections.
* Demonstrated ability to interpret complex medical records accurately while adhering to compliance standards.
* Prior experience in a medical office environment or healthcare facility is mandatory.
* Certification as a Certified Professional Coder (CPC), Certified Coding Specialist (CCS), or equivalent credential is required. Join our dedicated team as we uphold excellence in healthcare documentation through precise coding practices that support quality patient care and operational efficiency!

title: Wellness Manager RN/ LPN
description:
Easy Living Assistance is hiring for a Wellness Manager. The Wellness Manager RN/LPN is responsible for the planning, organization, direction, supervision and evaluation of all the nursing services provided in the facility. Ensures nursing department compliance with federal, state, and local regulations, implementation of company nursing core programs, orientation and training of nursing services personnel, and budget management.

**Wellness Manager RN/ LPN Duties and Responsibilities:**

* Manages the nursing staff, scheduling breaks, reassigning employees from one area to another area as facility needs dictate, writing performance reviews, and enforcing policies with responsibility to issue Coaching and Corrective Action, as needed.
* Responsible for recruitment, training, clinical orientation, supervision, scheduling, timecards, and personnel issues in the nursing department.
* Participates with the Medical Consultants and the Administrator in the selection of all potential new admissions to the facility and assess items needed in the facility to meet the new resident’s needs, admission, retention, and discharge of residents.
* Completes rounds of the facility at least daily to ensure compliance with all policies, procedures, and regulations.
* Collaborates with the Administrator in the planning of staff development programs that will enhance staff knowledge in providing quality resident care.
* Ensures each resident’s/patient’s RAI/IPOC process is carried out on a timely basis.
* Ensures the maintenance of licensure status for all nursing employees.
* Works with regional personnel to continuously improve the quality of resident/patient care.
* Supervises nursing department and assigns work to nursing staff and personal care staff as appropriate, including administration of medication, observation and reporting changes in resident’s conditions.
* Provides instruction and direction in methods and techniques of nursing and resident care.
* Ensures that care, comfort, and well\\-being of the resident are attained in accordance with established policies and procedures and in compliance with individual service plans.
* Assist with the assessments process. Also assists with admissions and discharges.
* Receive verbal orders from physicians including lab work, x\\-rays, etc.
* Verify medication orders with physician upon resident admission or discharge from hospital. Assist with resident health assessments.
* Supervise and assist residents with medications, including insulin injections and blood sugar checks.
* Ensures that resident service plans, charts and treatment schedules are followed by staff.
* Processes admission and discharges of residents.
* Provides information/updates to nursing staff, supervisors, administration, physicians, and other disciplines as appropriate to coordinate continuity of care.
* Conducts medication audits and handles medication errors in a timely manner.
* Assures medications are ordered as per licensed healthcare professional orders in a timely manner.
* Orders treatment supplies, resident care supplies, and nursing station supplies for assigned areas as needed.
* Assists and oversees care instruction during new hire orientation
* Maintains a high degree of safety awareness and infection control practices.
* Follows all state guidelines and regulations and policies with incident reporting.
* Assist as necessary with staffing issues, including finding coverage for call\\-offs.
* Ensures appropriate staffing levels are maintained, assisting in finding coverage and covering shifts, as needed.
* On call 24 hours a day for nursing emergencies. If out of town/not available, will designates a qualified registered nurse to assume such duties. The designee must be approved by the Administrator and appropriate facility personnel notified.
* Assess residents in the hospital to determine appropriateness for return.
* Second in command of the building. Leads and is responsible for the building if the Executive Director is unavailable.
* Performs other duties as directed by the Executive Director.
* Completes competency evaluations for training as required by the state or as assigned by their immediate supervisor, HR Director, or Executive Director.
* Responsible to issue employee discipline (oral and written), as appropriate and in consultation with the Executive Director, as necessary.
* Follow all applicable Federal and State regulations

**Wellness Manager RN/LPN Qualifications and Skills:**

* Proven strong management skills, including delegating responsibility to subordinates, performance management, conflict management, and leading through others.
* Must have good financial and management skills.
* Must be able to adapt to a flexible work schedule and occasional overnight.
* Be able to effectively communicate with a diverse range of audiences and settings: properly handle emotional situations, manage resources to accomplish resident care objectives, assess operational, staffing, and fiscal needs, analyze complex written documents, and work long and irregular hours.
* Ability to read, write, speak, and understand English.
* Demonstrates basic computer knowledge and ability with an aptitude to learn company applications as well as proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite (Excel, Work, Outlook, PowerPoint).

**Wellness Manager with RN/LPN Education and Experience:**

* Current Licensure Nursing Bachelor’s degree (RN) or a Licensed Practical Nurse (LPN)
* Current CPR and First Aid Certification
* Valid Michigan Driver License
* from an accredited School of Nursing, BSN preferred.
* Current LPN/ RN license with the state required.
* Previous assisted living management experience of at least three years.

**Physical Requirements:**

* Walking, reaching, bending, lifting, extended sitting, grasping, fine hand coordination, pushing and pulling, ability to distinguish smells and temperatures, all with or without the aid of mechanical devices is required.
* Limited potential for exposure to environmental hazards. Understanding and adherence to company safety standards and protocols required.
* Meet all health requirements as needed.

**Benefits:**

* 401(k)
* Supplement Medical insurance
* Life Insurance

title: Physical Therapist (PT)
description:
**PT with Purpose**

At Renew Integrative Physical Therapy, we believe that true healing for patients begins with humility, service, and purpose. We are a Christ\\-centered, self\\-pay orthopedic practice committed to honoring God in our work, putting others before ourselves, and restoring people to full wellness. This is more than a job – it’s a calling.

The medical system is broken and as reimbursements go down and the need for wholistic healing increases, there is a great need for a different kind of healing through physical therapy. PTs are already being replaced by A.I., online exercise protocols and other professions such as massage therapy. Only the PTs who invest in themselves and train to approach healing differently will be able to meet the demands of a changing healthcare climate.

We believe we are that industry disrupter that our system needs – not by chasing titles or status, but by becoming excellent in both skill and spirit. We are looking for remarkable individuals with strong character, a heart for service, and a relentless pursuit of growth – not simply years of experience.

If you are ready to grow into the clinician and person you were meant to be, read on.

**Opportunity Highlights**

· **Clinical Mentorship \\& Mastery**  
Train in advanced, cutting\\-edge techniques that go beyond traditional PT school curriculum. With deep mentorship and a focus on integrative healing, our team is elevated into the top 1% of clinicians in the country — both in outcomes and income.

· **Earn While You Learn**  
We believe “high requirements deserve high reward.” That’s why we provide full compensation and benefits even during training, so you can grow without the burden of financial stress.

· **Leadership Development \\& Ownership Pathways**  
We don’t just teach you how to treat – we equip you to lead. You’ll gain business acumen, leadership tools, and even the opportunity to open your own practice within our network, if that’s your calling.

**Who is Renew?**  
Renew Integrative Physical Therapy is a true industry disruptor – not because we chase trends, but because we return to what matters most: outcomes for clients. We put patients before paperwork and purpose above profit. Every decision we make is grounded in honoring God, serving others with compassion, and delivering exceptional outcomes.

We seek to understand the root cause of dysfunction and provide care that brings lasting healing, not just temporary relief. Our model empowers clinicians to spend quality time with patients, apply advanced techniques like Fascial Counterstrain, and solve the complex problems others overlook.

At Renew, excellence isn’t a buzzword — it’s a culture. We attract physical therapists who are hungry for growth, willing to be sharpened, and ready to lead a new standard of care. This is where mission meets mastery. If you're ready to make a difference and rise to your full potential, you're in the right place.

**Do You Have What It Takes to Join Renew?**

* **Full Commitment** – There is no halfway. We serve wholeheartedly.
* **Confidence** – Know what you know. Own what you don’t.
* **Humility** – Be teachable, flexible, and eager to grow.
* **Grit** – This path is not easy, but it’s worth it.

**Next Steps**

Only apply if you resonate with this mission and meet the criteria above. To be considered, please submit your resume and a cover letter that answers the following:

* Where do you see yourself in 5–10 years?
* What values are most important to you in an employer?
* What do you know about Fascial Counterstrain (if anything)?

**A Final Note**

We do not hire resumes – we hire people. We hire people who are bold in faith, humble in heart, relentless in pursuit, and deeply aligned with our mission to bring true healing to the world.

Job Type: Full\\-time

Pay: $85,000\\.00 \\- $95,000\\.00 per month

Benefits:

* 401(k) matching
* Flexible schedule
* Paid time off
